hypotheses.hypothesis: Files with empty content (no text) might contain bad data.
Files with filenames that contain a sequence of numbers followed by ".txt" but have no content may contain bad data.
Files with filenames that have a length greater than 10 characters and no content may contain bad data.
Files that contain a significantly higher number of numerical values within the content may contain bad data.
Files that contain an unusually high frequency of special characters within their content may contain bad data.
